{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"71519e2e-be94-42ff-b836-1fcd76a8bef9","content":"There's no pipeline file in the current directory, so here's the general migration guidance:\n\n## Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) isn't supported by VSTest@3. Use a `dotnet` task instead:\n\n**Before (VSTest@3):**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblies: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After (`dotnet test` with MTP):**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n## Key changes\n\n1. **Enable MTP** in each test `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n   <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   ```\n2. **TRX reports** — use `--logger trx`; publish with `PublishTestResults@2` (VSTest@3 did this automatically).\n3. **Code coverage** — use `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` and publish with `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2`. For Cobertura format add the `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` NuGet package and a `.runsettings` file if needed.\n4. **Test by project** (`**/*Tests.csproj`) instead of by assembly (`**/*.dll`), since MTP produces self-contained test executables.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4c5e41ca-3abe-423e-9caa-05e7f9130372","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps CI pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":617,"requestId":"1BF1:361109:21F9D70:2557C51:6A03CE74"},"id":"d37ea32b-7ee4-450f-b881-a5571bfe315a","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:06:07.718Z","parentId":"75389f0d-fc15-421f-9ae3-0e1e117ae7d0"}
